  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6997.27 sitting just below the massive 7000 gamma wall (17.9B), dealers are positioned to aggressively sell any push above this level as they hedge their long gamma exposure. The PIN regime confirms dealers will provide liquidity by selling rallies and buying dips, with the concentrated positive gamma cluster from 7000-7100 acting as a powerful magnet keeping price range-bound. Key levels to watch are the 6875 flip strike as downside support and the 7000 strike as immediate resistance, with dealers likely stepping in hard on any break above 7025 given the stacked gamma walls.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect price to get pulled back toward 7000 and stay locked in the 6900-7050 range.",
